===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|pund|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|punda-|lang=en}}, an early borrowing from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|pondo|pondō|lang=la}} in {{term|libra|lībra|lang=la}} {{term|pondo|pondō|lang=la}} ‘a pound by weight’ (a misinterpretation: {{term|pondo|pondō|lang=la}} is the adverb meaning ‘by weight’, originally an ablative form of {{term|pondus|lang=la}}). Cognate with Dutch {{term|pond|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Pfund|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|pund|lang=sv}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# Short for [[pound-force]], a unit of force/weight.
# A [[unit]] of [[mass]] equal to 16 [[avoirdupois]] ounces (= 453.592 37 g) or 12 [[troy weight|troy ounce]]s (≈ 373.242 g). Its symbol is [[lb]].
# {{US}} The symbol # ([[octothorpe]], [[hash]]) <!--isn't this "pound sign" rather than "pound"?-->
# A unit of [[currency]] used in Cyprus; Egypt; Lebanon; the United Kingdom and its [[dependency|dependencies]]; and formerly in the Republic of Ireland (which now uses the [[euro]]) and Israel (which now uses the [[sheqel]]). Its symbol is <big>[[£]]</big>.

